# GIS Toolbox — project rules

## Stack

- **Vite + React app**: `index.html` → `#root` → `react/main.jsx` → `react/App.jsx`.
- **Build/preview**: `npm run dev`, `npm run build`, `npm run preview`. Browser checks via preview (`npm run smoke:preview`), not a static file server.
- **Tests**: `npm test` (Vitest). Map/UI changes still need manual browser verification.
- **Map**: MapLibre bundled via npm (`bootstrapGlobals`). Imperative map service in `js/map/` — not in the React render tree.
- **Domain logic**: `js/` — import/export, transforms, GIS tools, workflow engine, widgets.

## Where to change what

- **UI shell**: `react/App.jsx`, `react/panels/`, `react/tools/`, `react/workflow/`.
- **Handlers & wiring**: `js/tools/tool-handlers.js` — `APP_ACTIONS`, bus wiring, drag/drop, session restore.
- **State**: `js/core/state.js`, `react/providers/AppStore.jsx` (Zustand bridge).
- **New import/export formats**: `js/import/` or `js/export/` plus registration in importer/exporter entry modules.
- **Pipeline nodes**: `js/workflow/nodes/`, `js/workflow/node-catalog.js`, `react/workflow/inspectors/`.
- **GIS Widgets** (multi-step wizards): read `docs/WIDGET_AUTHORING.md`; register in `js/widgets/registry.js`; engine in `js/widgets/<id>/`, UI in `react/widgets/`.
- **GIS Tools** (single-shot dialogs): `js/tools/gis-tools.js` + `react/tools/`.
- **Styling**: `css/`; mobile gate in `react/shell/MobileGate.jsx` + `css/mobile.css`.

## Quality bar

- Preserve existing error handling (`handleError`, toasts, logger).
- Match surrounding code style (semicolons, quote style, comment density).
- After behavior changes, run `npm test`; after map or UI changes, also sanity-check in a browser (`npm run preview`).
- Read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` before structural changes.
